**Definition**
Transitions in jQuery Mobile are animated effects used when navigating between pages, providing smooth visual movement.

**Types**

* slide
* fade
* pop
* flip
* turn
* flow
* slideup / slidedown

**Working**
When a link is clicked, jQuery Mobile applies a CSS-based animation between the current page and the target page using `data-transition`.

**Diagrams (text)**

```
Page A --(slide)--> Page B
Page A --(fade)-->  Page B
```

**Advantages**

* Enhances user experience
* Makes navigation feel natural
* Wide variety of built-in effects

**Disadvantages**

* Can feel slow on older devices
* Too many transitions can distract users

**Examples**

```html
<a href="#about" data-transition="slide">Slide</a>
<a href="#info" data-transition="fade">Fade</a>
```

**Short code snippets**

```html
<a href="#home" data-transition="pop">Pop Transition</a>
```

**Applications**

* Navigation between pages
* Dialog opening animations
* Smooth mobile UI interactions
